Germany’s Rich Could Pay $138 Billion in Taxes, Rundschau Says

-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s
-- 
2011-10-15T10:41:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-15/germany-s-rich-could-pay-138-billion-in-taxes-rundschau-says.html
German millionaires could contribute
as much as 100 billion euros ($138 billion) in additional tax
revenue to help improve social justice and the country’s budget,
 Frankfurter Rundschau  said, citing an interview with Gert
Wagner, chief executive of Berlin’s DIW economic institute.  To contact the reporter on this story:
